        <p id="My_Life_Story_by_Randy_Bird_Several_years_ago_I_heard_a_talk_t">
        <span id="textspanz3">My Life Story<br /></span><span id="textspanz4">Randy Bird<br /><br /></span><span id="textspanz5">Several years ago I heard a <a id="underline" href="http://magazine.byu.edu/?act=view&a=1292">talk</a> that helped me define who I am, who I should be and who I'd eventually become. There were three themes: preside, provide, and protect. Those three themes have been very instrumental in shaping my life goals. To preside over my family meant that they knew there was someone in charge, that he followed the Lord and led the family according to His goals and His mission. To provide was to take care of my family, so my wife and children could rely on my providing for their needs. In my mind, to protect meant to be a defender of the family, against things that could harm it.<br /><br />Those three roles were very important. As I look back over the life I've led, it's easy to put all my decisions into those three categories. I did "x" because of my three responsibilities to preside, provide and protect. By focusing on these three things, I've added tremendous value and meaning to my life.</span> 
        </p>
